<tr><td valign=top colspan=5><table border=0 width="100%"><tr><td><font size="+1"><B><a name="815">Fairy</a></B> / IPD No. <a class="linkid"  href="machine.cgi?id=815">815</a> <I>/ September, 1975 / 1 Player</I></font><br>&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=top></td></tr></table></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=top align=right><b>Average Fun Rating: </b></td><td colspan=4 width="80%" align=left valign=top><font color=red>Needs More Ratings!</font> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font color="#666666">6.6 / 10</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;(<a href="rate/showrate.pl?gid=815" target="showrate815">2 ratings</a>)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[ <a href="rate/login.pl?gid=815" target="do_a_rating">Add Your Rating!</a> ]
</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Manufacturer: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline><span title="Click here to perform a search for all pinball games manufactured by 'Playmatic'"><a href="search.pl?searchtype=advanced&amp;mfgid=255">Playmatic, <font size="-1">of Barcelona, Spain</font> (1968-1987)</a></span></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Date Of Manufacture: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>September, 1975</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Type: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>Electro-mechanical (EM)&nbsp;<a href="showhelp.pl?item=type&amp;highlight=EM#EM" title="Show Type Classifications" target="help"><img alt="[?]" style="cursor: help;" src="/graphic/question.gif" border=0></a></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" align="right" valign=baseline><b>Serial Number Database:</b></td><td colspan=4 align="left" valign=baseline><a href="redirect.pl?http://www.ipsnd.net/View.aspx?id=815">View at <I>The Internet Pinball Serial Number Database</I> (IPSND.net)</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size="-1"><I>(External site)</i></font></td></tr><tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Theme: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>Fantasy</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Notable Features: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline><a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Flipper">Flippers</a> (2), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Pop_Bumper">Pop&nbsp;bumper</a> (1), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Slingshot">Slingshots</a> (2), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Standup_Target">Standup&nbsp;targets</a> (7), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Spinning_Target">Spinning&nbsp;target</a> (1), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Kick-out_Hole">Kick-out&nbsp;hole</a> (1), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Captive_Ball">Captive&nbsp;ball</a> (1), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Action_Ring">Action&nbsp;ring</a>. <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Wedge_Head">Wedge&nbsp;head</a> <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Backbox">backbox</a>. 3 or 5 ball play.<br><br>Maximum displayed point score is 999,990 points.<P></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Notes: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>The 4-player version of this game is <span title="Click here to open a new window and display Playmatic's 1976 'Fantasy'"><a target="game3090" href="machine.cgi?id=3090">Playmatic's 1976 'Fantasy'</a></span>.<br><br>The <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Playfield">playfield</a> layout is a near-copy of the 2-player <span title="Click here to open a new window and display Bally's 1975 'Flicker'"><a target="game883" href="machine.cgi?id=883">Bally's 1975 'Flicker'</a></span> and the 4-player <span title="Click here to open a new window and display Bally's 1974 'Boomerang'"><a target="game354" href="machine.cgi?id=354">Bally's 1974 'Boomerang'</a></span>.<br><br>The man and woman on the <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Backglass">backglass</a> look similar to the couple depicted on the <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Backglass">backglass</a> of <span title="Click here to open a new window and display Gottlieb's 1975 'Atlantis'"><a target="game105" href="machine.cgi?id=105">Gottlieb's 1975 'Atlantis'</a></span>.<P></td></tr>
